node.text:
@USANAinc Active Nutrition is here!!🥳 this Electrolyte Replacement is part of it and essential for the summer heat. .Sponsored 

Dressing
* 3 tbsp olive oil
* 3 tbsp lime juice
* 3 garlic clove, minced
* 2 packets Electrolyte Replacement
For the salad
* 5 cups cubed watermelon 
* 1/4 cup Blueberries
* 1/3 Cup Cucumbers
* 1 medium Avocado, cubed 
* 1/2 Serrano Pepper, sliced
* 2 oz. Feta Cheese, crumbled
* mint to taste
* Sea salt and pepper to taste 
Instructions:
Now let’s get started. First whisk together all dressing ingredients. Set aside. 
Assemble the salad ingredients on a platter as desired. Feel free to add or substitute ingredients as you like! Season to taste and serve with dressing. Perfect for the summer!#LiveUSANA  #USANAactive #salad #summer #watermelon #hydrate

node.title: Watermelon Salad with hydrating watermelon dressing 🥗🍉

node.text:
Stuffed Jalapeños with mozzarella, ricotta and parmigiano. By @themodernnonna

Are you drooling yet? Me too! These are my moms very accidental creation as she randomly decided to stuff jalapeños when she had extra ricotta mixture from the eggplant rolls she was making years ago. They were absolutely the most delicious jalapeños I have ever had and I knew I couldn’t keep them a secret for much longer. If you are a lover of jalapeños, you will go to heaven and back with this recipe. You will need:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
14 Jalapeños ( seeded )
3/4-1 cup ricotta
1 egg ( or leave it out )
salt to taste
1/2 cup grated parmigiano
1-1.5 cups marinara ( “or as much as you like)
1/2 cup mozzarella (or as much as you like)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Please note: You can leave out the egg if you are intolerant. Feel free to use any marinara like @raoshomemade which is clean in ingredients. You are more than welcome to add basil to the ricotta but it’s up to you. If you can’t handle any heat then stuff mini bell peppers instead. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Pre-heat oven to 400F. Wash and cut the ends of the Jalapeños and discard the seeds with a knife or a spoon but be gentle. In a separate bowl add the ricotta , parm , egg , dash of salt and mix. Take a small pan (we used 8 by 8) and add marinara sauce to cover the bottom ( we used our own homemade sugo which is on my highlights but you can use any store bought like rao’s) Take each jalapeño and with a tiny spoon or a piping bag add ricotta mixture to each one making sure you push it down gently. Add them all to your baking dish , top with more marinara and some mozzarella. Bake at 400F for 35-40 minutes or until nice and melted and the peppers are soft but also have a bite to them. Enjoy, and follow me for more.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
✨THE Egg Sandwich ✨
A breakfast staples and it’s easy peasy by @thecuttingveg 🔥 

Here’s how we will break it down. First, toast an English muffin, then layer on hummus, avocado, scrambled eggs, arugula, and hot sauce. 😛 I also love adding pickled red onions to be fancy but I wasn’t feeling fancy this time . She’s still a beauty!!
The deets: breakfast sandwich with scrambled eggs, avocado, pickled onions, arugula, and Italian bomba spread.

pickled red onions 
-
1 red onion, thinly sliced
1/2 cup apple cider vinegar
1/2 cup warm water
1/2 tablespoon sugar (if using honey or maple syrup, use a little less)
1/2 teaspoon salt
Optional mix ins (dried dill/peppercorns/fennel seeds/ginger slices/cumin seeds)
meanderings
In a small bowl, whisk together apple cider vinegar, water, sugar, and salt until the sugar and salt dissolve. Add your mix ins (if using) to the brine and stir to combine.
Place sliced red onion in a mason jar (I like to use a wide mouthed mason jar, but any type will do!) Pour brine over onions. If the brine does not completely cover the onions, top the jar off with more water. Screw on lid and place in the fridge for a minimum of 2 hours.
The onions will keep in the fridge for up to 2 weeks. You may use the leftover brine to create more onions. Simply add more sliced red onions to the brine and allow to sit in the fridge for 2 hours. EAT

node.text:
This Quick Mushroom Rice is the perfect dish.  I'm using @seedsofchange Organic Brown Basmati Rice.  It has a wonderful aroma and unique, slightly nutty flavor.  This good for you super grain makes for a nutritious addition to any meal. Enjoy this dish as a meatless main course or add to your favorite meat as a side.  It is super delicious and filling either way.  Enjoy SEEDS OF CHANGE by itself too and it’s ready in just 90 seconds! 
 
1 package (8.5-ounce) SEEDS OF CHANGE™ Organic Brown Basmati Rice
2 tbsp Olive Oil
3 cloves garlic
1/2 cup diced shallot 
3 cups mushrooms pieces and stems
1/2 cup parmesan cheese
1 tbsp water
fresh parsley, chopped
salt and pepper to Taste
 
Instructions:
Heat skillet over medium-high heat.  Once warm, add the oil. Add Garlic and saute for 30 seconds. 
 
Add the shallot and mushrooms, cook until tender.
 
Now empty 1 package (8.5-ounce) @seedsofchange Organic Brown Basmati Rice into your pan, breaking apart any large pieces.
 
Add one tbsp water.  Season to taste with salt and pepper.  Cook until warm, about 3 minutes. 
 
Add parmesan cheese and stir until combined. 
 
Top with chopped parsley. 
 
Serve hot.
 
THE POWER IN YOUR PURCHASE
For every food item you buy,  SEEDS OF CHANGE partners with national nonprofit FoodCorps to plant nutritious seeds through school growing programs across the country. With your help, SEEDS OF CHANGE is putting more plants on plates every day. #BeASeedOfChange

Sun Dried Tomato Corn Chowder with Crispy Goat Cheese Croutons 🌽 corn is ready here and sweet as can be. By @howsweeteats

•	1 tablespoon olive oil
* 1 small sweet onion, diced
* 2 garlic cloves, minced
* ½ teaspoon salt
* ½ teaspoon freshly ground pepper
* ½ teaspoon smoked paprika
* ¼ cup chopped sun dried tomatoes, drain if they are in oil, plus more for topping
* 2 cups corn kernels, cut fresh from the cob, plus extra for topping
* 1 ½ cups chopped yukon gold potatoes
* 4 cups chicken or vegetable stock
* 1 1/2 cups half and half
* 1 1/2 tablespoons flour
* ¼ cup fresh chopped chives
GOAT CHEESE CROUTONS
* 1 11 ounce log goat cheese (cold, right from the fridge)
* ¼ cup flour
* 1 large egg, lightly beaten
* 1 cup seasoned bread crumbs
* olive oil, for pan frying
Instructions 
* Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium-low heat. Stir in the onions and garlic with a pinch of salt and pepper and smoked paprika and cook, stirring often, until softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the chopped sun dried tomatoes and cook for another 1 to 2 minutes.
* Stir in the corn, potatoes and stock. Bring the mixture to a boil, reduce it to a simmer and cover, cooking until the potatoes are fork tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
* While the soup simmers, make the goat cheese croutons. Slice the goat cheese into rounds - this can be as many rounds as you want, but I do 6 or so. Place the flour on one plate, the beaten egg on another and the breadcrumbs on a third. Heat a large skillet over medium heat and add 2 tablespoons olive oil. Dip each goat cheese piece in flour, then in egg, then in breadcrumbs. Place it in the hot oil and cook for 1ish minute per side until it’s golden and crispy. Remove with a slotted spoon and place it on a paper towel to remove excess grease.
* In a shaker bottle, add the flour to the half and half and shake well until it is combined. Slowly pour it into the soup mixture while stirring. Simmer the mixture for 5 minutes – it should thicken up. Taste and season additionally if needed. Stir in most of the chives, reserving a few for topping.
* Serve, topping the bowl with extra sun dried tomatoes, fresh corn off the cob and a goat cheese crouton!

node.text:
🍫🍦Chocolate ice cream
Easy to make, dairy-free and delicious, a must try for sure! 
By @wholesomehedonista
Ingredients
* 1 can full fat coconut cream- brands can be very different I recommend Thai kitchen or Trader Joe’s brand 
* 1/3 cup almond milk 
* 2 tbsp cashew butter salted
* 1/3 cup + 1 tbsp cocoa powder
* 1/3 cup pure maple syrup
* 1/2 tsp vanilla
* small pinch salt
Instructions
* Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.  
* Pour into an ice cube tray (it should fit into just one its ok if very full they'll come out easily). 
* Freeze overnight (at least 8 hours, until firm)  
* Blend ice cubes in a high powered blender with a small splash of almond milk if needed until smooth and creamy. Use tamper if you have a vitamix or stop machine and scrape down the sides until fully blended. Careful not to blend too long or it will melt 
* Enjoy as creamy soft serve or transfer to a freezer safe container and freeze about 4-6 hours covered until firm and scoopable.  
* Let thaw 10-15 minutes at room temp to soften. Hope you enjoy ❤️

#dairyfree #veganicecream #vegandessert #dairyfreeicecream #nicecream #dairyfreedessert #chocolateicecream #paleovegan #dairyfreeketo #veganketo #healthydessert
